 ### 1) `GET /csrf-token`
 Returns an anonymous CSRF token and sets `anon_csrf` cookie.
 
+Clients must send the returned token in `X-CSRF-TOKEN` on anonymous state-changing auth
+requests. The server validates the header against the `anon_csrf` cookie.
+
 ### 2) `POST /register`
 Creates a user account (does not auto-login).
 
